## Parallel Fan-Out with CompletableFuture

### The Problem — Sequential = Additive Latency

```java
// BEFORE: sequential — total = 200 + 600 + 300 + 300 = 1400ms
public ProductPageDto loadProductPage(String userId, String productId) {
    UserProfile   profile    = userService.getProfile(userId);        // 200ms
    List<Order>   orders     = orderService.getRecentOrders(userId);  // 600ms
    WalletBalance wallet     = walletService.getBalance(userId);      // 300ms
    List<Product> recs       = recommendationService.get(productId);  // 300ms
    return new ProductPageDto(profile, orders, wallet, recs);
}
```

### Step 1 — Dedicated Thread Pool for I/O-Bound Calls

```java
@Configuration
public class AsyncConfig {
    // I/O-bound: use 2x–4x core count threads
    @Bean(name = "serviceCallExecutor")
    public Executor serviceCallExecutor() {
        ThreadPoolTaskExecutor executor = new ThreadPoolTaskExecutor();
        executor.setCorePoolSize(20);
        executor.setMaxPoolSize(50);
        executor.setQueueCapacity(100);
        executor.setThreadNamePrefix("svc-call-");
        executor.setRejectedExecutionHandler(new ThreadPoolExecutor.CallerRunsPolicy());
        executor.initialize();
        return executor;
    }
}
```

### Step 2 — Fan-Out: Launch All Calls in Parallel

```java
@Service
public class ProductPageAggregator {

    @Autowired @Qualifier("serviceCallExecutor")
    private Executor executor;

    public ProductPageDto loadProductPage(String userId, String productId) {
        // Capture MDC for correlation ID propagation across threads
        Map<String, String> mdcContext = MDC.getCopyOfContextMap();

        // Fan-out: all four calls launch simultaneously
        CompletableFuture<UserProfile> profileFuture = CompletableFuture
            .supplyAsync(() -> withMdc(mdcContext, () -> userService.getProfile(userId)), executor)
            .orTimeout(500, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS);

        CompletableFuture<List<Order>> ordersFuture = CompletableFuture
            .supplyAsync(() -> withMdc(mdcContext, () -> orderService.getRecentOrders(userId)), executor)
            .orTimeout(800, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS);

        CompletableFuture<WalletBalance> walletFuture = CompletableFuture
            .supplyAsync(() -> withMdc(mdcContext, () -> walletService.getBalance(userId)), executor)
            .orTimeout(500, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS);

        // Non-critical: return empty list if it fails (completeOnTimeout = graceful degradation)
        CompletableFuture<List<Product>> recsFuture = CompletableFuture
            .supplyAsync(() -> withMdc(mdcContext, () -> recommendationService.get(productId)), executor)
            .completeOnTimeout(Collections.emptyList(), 400, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS)
            .exceptionally(ex -> {
                log.warn("recommendation-service failed, degrading gracefully: {}", ex.getMessage());
                return Collections.emptyList();
            });

        // Fan-in: wait for ALL to complete
        CompletableFuture.allOf(profileFuture, ordersFuture, walletFuture, recsFuture).join();

        return new ProductPageDto(
            profileFuture.join(),
            ordersFuture.join(),
            walletFuture.join(),
            recsFuture.join()
        );
    }

    private <T> T withMdc(Map<String, String> ctx, Supplier<T> task) {
        MDC.setContextMap(ctx != null ? ctx : Collections.emptyMap());
        try { return task.get(); } finally { MDC.clear(); }
    }
}
```

### Result

```
BEFORE — sequential:  200 + 600 + 300 + 300 = 1400ms total
AFTER  — parallel:    max(200, 600, 300, 300) =  600ms total  ✅ (57% faster)

Thread: svc-call-1 → userService    (200ms) ─────────┐
Thread: svc-call-2 → orderService   (600ms) ──────────────────┐
Thread: svc-call-3 → walletService  (300ms) ────────────┐     │
Thread: svc-call-4 → recommendationService (timeout)    │     │
                     returns [] at 400ms ──────────┐    │     │
                                                   └────┴─────┘ allOf.join()
                                                              t=600ms → response
```

### Partial Failure Strategy

```java
// Classify calls by criticality
// CRITICAL (page fails if these fail): profile, wallet
// NON-CRITICAL (degrade gracefully):   orders, recommendations

CompletableFuture<UserProfile> profileFuture = CompletableFuture
    .supplyAsync(() -> userService.getProfile(userId), executor)
    .orTimeout(500, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS);
    // No exceptionally — let it propagate; profile is mandatory

CompletableFuture<List<Order>> ordersFuture = CompletableFuture
    .supplyAsync(() -> orderService.getRecentOrders(userId), executor)
    .orTimeout(800, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS)
    .exceptionally(ex -> {
        log.warn("order-service degraded: {}", ex.getMessage());
        return Collections.emptyList();   // show empty order list
    });
```

### Micrometer Metrics for Parallel Calls

```java
// Time the entire fan-out/fan-in
Timer.Sample sample = Timer.start(meterRegistry);
CompletableFuture.allOf(profileFuture, ordersFuture, walletFuture, recsFuture).join();
sample.stop(meterRegistry.timer("product.page.load"));

// Per-service counters
if (recsFuture.isCompletedExceptionally()) {
    meterRegistry.counter("recommendation.service.degraded").increment();
}
```

